<topic id="bfdca13a-e0ad-4b84-9cc7-b1d3809b663f" revisionNumber="1">
	<developerConceptualDocument
    xmlns="http://ddue.schemas.microsoft.com/authoring/2003/5"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
		<introduction>
			<para>Adding a new size to an existing font in the application can be accomplished through this feature. Sizes are a collection of base images and variants.</para>
			<para>
				<mediaLink>
					<image placement="center" xlink:href="Add-New-Font-Size"/>
				</mediaLink>
			</para>
		</introduction>
		<section address="VariantsContextMenu">
			<title>Variants Context Menu</title>
			<content>
				<para>Right-clicking the variants area exposes the following context menu actions:</para>
				<list class="ordered">
					<listItem>
						<para>
							<legacyBold>Add Variant</legacyBold>: This feature adds a new variant to the size.
						</para>
					</listItem>
					<listItem>
						<para>
							<legacyBold>Edit Variant</legacyBold>: This feature edits an existing variant in the size.
						</para>
					</listItem>
					<listItem>
						<para>
							<legacyBold>Remove Variant</legacyBold>: This feature removes an existing variant from a size.
						</para>
					</listItem>
				</list>
			</content>
		</section>
		<relatedTopics />
	</developerConceptualDocument>
</topic>
